underlying_goal: Back up an SSH config file and commit and push pending changes to a git repository.
primary_success: Successfully handled a git rebase during the push process, correctly identifying that a conflicting change was already present on the remote and completing the rebase cleanly.
brief_summary: The user requested to back up their SSH config and push pending changes. The agent ran the backup script, then initiated a commit and push. It encountered a change on the remote, performed a rebase to integrate changes, and successfully pushed.
